subSubSection.paragraph:
Legs
.

Relatively short, stout; all coxae large, with polygonal reticulate sculpture (only visible under layer of air, Figs 
4D
, 
5B
); protibia with long, curved, bifurcate calcar, with strong, straight, socketed seta and three stout setae along anteroapical margin (Fig. 
6A
); strigil and basitarsal comb present (Fig. 
6A
); tarsi 5-segmented; mesotibia with thick mesotibial spur, about as long as mesobasitarsus (Figs 
4G
, 
6B
), and with row of pegs along anteroapical edge (Fig. 
4G
); ventral surface of mesobasitarsus and each next tarsomere with row of setae and irregular pattern of pegs along anteroventral edge (Fig. 
6B
); metatibia with two spurs.
